AWS Storage Services  

1. Object Storage — Amazon S3 (Simple Storage Service)
Store any type of file (images, videos, PDFs, backups) as objects in buckets.   

Feature                      Detail

Type                         Flat storage (no folders, just keys)
Access                       Via URL / API
Scalability                  Unlimited
Durability                   99.999999999% (11 9s)

S3 Storage Classes (When to use what):

S3 Standard: Frequently accessed data (websites, apps)
S3 Intelligent-Tiering: Unknown or changing access patterns  
S3 Standard-IA (Infrequent Access): Accessed once a month (backups)
S3 Glacier: Long-term archiving, retrieved in minutes
S3 Glacier Deep Archive: Rarely accessed, cheapest, retrieved in hours.

 Use S3 when: storing media files, hosting static websites, data lakes, backups, and logs.

2. Block Storage — Amazon EBS (Elastic Block Store)
Think of EBS like a hard drive attached to your EC2 server. It stores data in fixed-size blocks, just like your laptop's SSD.

Feature                     Detail
Attached to                 EC2 instances only
Access                      Like a local disk
Persistence                 Data stays even if EC2 stops
Type                        SSD or HDD-based

Use EBS when: running databases, OS storage for EC2, applications needing low-latency disk access

3. File Storage — Amazon EFS (Elastic File System) & FSx
Think of EFS like a shared network drive — multiple servers can access the same files simultaneously.  

Feature                      Detail
Type                         Managed NFS (Network File System)
Access                       Multiple EC2s at the same time
OS                           SupportLinux only
Scaling                      Auto-scales as data grows

Use EFS when: multiple EC2 instances need shared access to same files (web servers sharing assets, ML training data)


other services:
AWS Snow Family (Snowball, Snowcone, Snowmobile)
Physical devices to transfer massive amounts of data to AWS when the internet upload is too slow. Imagine shipping a hard drive to Amazon!  


Need to store files/media/backups?         → S3
Need a hard disk for your EC2?             → EBS
Multiple servers sharing same files?       → EFS
Windows file sharing?                      → FSx for Windows
High-performance computing storage?        → FSx for Lustre
Hybrid (on-prem + cloud)?                 → Storage Gateway
Transferring petabytes of data?            → Snowball


